    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok, This is going to be hard to explain.  First of all the fellowship is an event deck, and the one event that is in there that shuffles deck is there so i dont get so many still neededs ever turn.  Basic archery, since i cant put doubleshot or break the charge etc in it.  Remember, no rares, so legolas has to have naith bow and his sword.  The legolas chosen was pretty dumb, because there is only one threat removal card in there, but what other legolas is there to use?  Ok, Shadow side, basically the easterlings have their damage plus 1 and my southrons basically spend too much twilight to wound the crap out of companions.  Simple as that, and anyone can build it.  OH, another thing, there is site liberation for c/u decks that use site control (probably the best thing) and there is anti archery (stupid goblin archery) so it counters all the good c/u decks.  I hope it does well </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
